comments.body:
Hi, My name is Jason Ksepka. I am the Curator at Bowman's Hill Wildflower Preserve in New Hope, Pa.
I am particularly interested in propagating this species becaus it is rapidly dropping out of the landscape due to weevils and deer.
If the number of seeds available is appropriate o make ethical collections, and you would be willing to send me some to propagate, could you please email me at ksepka@bhwp.org? Thank You, Awesome find!

Hi, My name is Jason Ksepka. I am the Curator at Bowman's Hill Wildflower Preserve in New Hope, Pa.
I am particularly interested in propagating this species becaus it is rapidly dropping out of the landscape due to weevils and deer.
If the number of seeds available is appropriate o make ethical collections, and you would be willing to send me some to propagate, could you please email me at ksepka@bhwp.org? Thank You, Awesome find!

results.description: AKA Thicket bean, the host plant for the rare Golden-banded Skipper. I learned from local experts that this skipper does not host on Hog peanut as is widely reported (in Wikipedia and elsewhere) - though hog peanut grows profusely in the same area. The second photo shows a skipper caterpillar tent on thicket bean, possibly golden-banded but could be other related species. Didn't disturb it to find out.
